Why would this be a "terrible idea"? Is it mostly that with a machine that has very few cores, the algorithm is dominated by communication among the different processes?

@jwhui I'm fine with the current solution.

But maybe we should propose this change to be included in the specification.

I can easily imagine situation where node with OpenThread stack may have problem to send MPL messages to nodes with other Thread stack. e.g. after reset (in worst case other nodes will not hear up to 27 MPL messages)

